menu "breadboard: bb_storage"

config BB_STORAGE_MAX_BACKENDS
    int "Storage backend registry capacity"
    default 4
    help
        Maximum number of registered backends (e.g. "nvs", "sdcard", "ram")
        in the static registry. Each entry costs sizeof(a name pointer + a
        4-function vtable + a context pointer). Registering more backends
        than this returns BB_ERR_NO_SPACE.

config BB_STORAGE_TXN_MAX_KEYS
    int "Multi-key transaction slot capacity"
    default 3
    range 3 32
    help
        Maximum number of distinct keys a single bb_storage_txn_t can stage
        (matches wifi-pending ssid/pass/try). Staging a new key once a
        transaction's slot table is full returns BB_ERR_NO_SPACE.

        Floored at 3: bb_storage_rtc (components/bb_storage_rtc) stages
        exactly 3 fixed keys (ssid/pass/provisioned) per commit -- a lower
        cap would make its transaction path always spuriously fail with
        BB_ERR_NO_SPACE.

config BB_STORAGE_TXN_VALUE_MAX_BYTES
    int "Multi-key transaction max staged value size (bytes)"
    default 64
    range 63 4096
    help
        Maximum size in bytes of a single value staged within a
        bb_storage_txn_t (covers a 63-byte WiFi password). A
        bb_storage_txn_set() call exceeding this returns BB_ERR_NO_SPACE.

        Floored at 63: bb_storage_rtc's "pass" field allows up to 63
        non-NUL bytes -- a lower cap would make staging a max-length WiFi
        password through the "rtc" backend always spuriously fail.

config BB_STORAGE_ENTRY_LIST_CAP
    int "Recommended bb_storage_list_entries() caller-side array capacity"
    default 32
    help
        NOT enforced inside bb_storage -- bb_storage_list_entries() is a
        pure caller-allocated-array API and never itself consults this
        value (see bb_storage.h). Documents the recommended
        bb_storage_entry_t[] array size for callers enumerating a
        backend's entries (e.g. bb_storage_nvs, the storage diag section)
        so they share one house-wide cap instead of each picking an
        arbitrary number.

endmenu
